d and all other keys/values remain identical.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Pairwise: Unit vs Integration -> Integration wins first because multiple modules (branching, commit prep, PR client) interact. Integration vs System -> System wins because behavior explicitly requires PR creation on the real repository; mocking would hide auth/API/git diff integration failures. Rejection gate: rejected Agentic/Workflow since no AI model decision is part of correctness; this is real git/HTTP infrastructure.","test_description":"Execute scanner end-to-end against a disposable real test repo and actual VCS hosting API credentials; assert PR exists remotely and its diff contains exactly one dependency version change with no unrelated file modifications.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.86,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Pairwise: Unit vs Integration -> Unit wins because this is deterministic semver comparison logic in one boundary. Unit vs System (winner check) -> Unit remains since no real infrastructure needed. Rejection gate: rejected higher levels because behavior text is purely semver rule evaluation, no module handoff requirement.","test_description":"Test semver comparator with cases like 1.2.3->2.0.0 (breaking), 1.2.3->1.3.0 (non-breaking), prerelease/build metadata variants; assert breaking-change boolean is correct.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.93,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pairwise: Unit vs Integration -> Integration wins because failure occurs at orchestration boundary (semver decision handed to PR creator and reporter). Integration vs System -> Integration wins because skip-PR behavior can be validated with an in-process fake PR client and output collector; real network is not required for this specific gate logic. Rejection gate: rejected System since behavior says PR is skipped, so real repository interaction is not required to catch failure; rejected Agentic/Workflow due to no AI decision steps.","test_description":"Wire scanner pipeline with semver detector + PR service mock + report formatter. Feed a breaking bump case and assert PR client was not invoked and scanner output includes explicit review-required flag.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
